txt.en: 'Where there are goblins, there are almost certainly Wargs. And this place is no exception.\n\n'Those accursed Wargs are everywhere around here. We must thin out their numbers before they smell us out and hunt us down.'
'That is one more pack of the flea-bitten beasts that we will not have to worry about. Good work, [placeholder].'
'Have you dealt with the Wargs yet?'
Wargs allied with the goblins haunt the western reaches of Nan Curunír, much to Ondor's chagrin.
Wargs roam the western reaches of Nan Curunír.\n\nOndor is concerned that, left unchecked, the Wargs will eventually converge on his location.
Talk to Ondor in Nan Curunír
Ondor is encamped near the caves in western Nan Curunír.\n\nYou should tell Ondor that you have managed to defeat a fair number of the Isen Wargs.
